"""## Bias Trick

Make sure that `X` takes into consideration the bias $\theta_0$ in the linear model. Hint, recall that the predications of our linear model are of the form:

$$
\hat{y} = h_\theta(x) = \theta^T x = \theta_0 + \theta_1 x_1
